translated: Årman, Karl Gustaf, physician, Jönköping, b. 22/6/01 in Gustafs, Kopparb. 1st district, son of district supervisor A.G. Ärman and Maria Andersson. Married in 1937 to Torborg Maria Gerdner, holder of a Bachelor of Philosophy degree. Children: Torborg Anita b. 1939, Tryggve b. 1941, Birgit b. 1943, Nils-Gustaf b. 1945. Completed secondary school examination in Stockholm in 1922, Bachelor of Medicine in 1925, and Doctor of Medicine in 1930, all at Uppsala University. Traveled to Germany, Switzerland, Czechoslovakia, and Austria. Worked as a doctor at Djursätra brunn from 1926 to 1930, temporary assistant doctor at Jönköping hospital in 1931, doctor at the medical department there from 1931 to 1932, and assistant physician from 1932 to 1934. Temporary second assistant doctor at Epidemic Hospital in Stockholm in 1934, practicing physician in Jönköping since 1934, temporary district physician there from 1936 to 1939, and physician at Epidemic Hospital from 1936 to 1939. Disposing physician in 1937.
